frameDefinitions: These words refer to Parts merging to form a Whole.
An Agent manipulates a linear entity (the Rope) to form a Knot.
An Agent creates a Knot (possibly in a Place and/or with an Instrument).'
An Agent brings about the end of a Theme's captivity at a Location_of_confinement in contravention of the plans or desires of a captor.
The words in this frame refer to what Clothing the Wearer (or a specific Body_part of the Wearer) has on.
An Item is attached by a Handle, via a Connector, to a Goal, or Items are attached to each other.
frameExamples: The two droplets <t>merge</t>, and then travel down the windowpane even faster.
Harry <t>tied</t> the rope into a slipknot.
Loretta <t>ties</t> the most beautiful bowline I've ever seen.
His accomplice <t>freed</t> him from Sing Sing prison thanks to his disguise.
I <t>had</t> <t>on</t> the most ridiculous monkey-suit you could imagine.
My thumb was <t>stuck</t> to the tube of glue.
listRoleDefinitions: The entities that merge to form a single <fen>Whole</fen>.
The single, undifferentiated entity that is the result of the amalgamation.
The prominent entity that combines with <fen>Part_2</fen> to form a <fen>Whole</fen>.
The less focussed-upon entity that the <fen>Part_1</fen> merges with.
The time at which the <fen>Parts</fen> become amalgamated into a <fen>Whole</fen>
The location at which the amalgamation occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the sentient being who manipulates the <fen>Rope</fen>.
The basically linear object which is manipulated by the <fen>Agent</fen> to produce a <fen>Knot</fen>.
The stable configuration of a <fen>Rope</fen> which results from tying.
When the manipulation of the <fen>Rope</fen> takes place.
Where the manipulation of the <fen>Rope</fen> takes place.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act.
The stable configuration of a String which results from tying.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual who ends the confinement or captivity of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the person or object in motion released by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The location to which the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion was formerly inhibited.
The <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Agent</fen> release the <fen>Theme</fen> .
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ceases to be confined.
The person whose clothing is under discussion.
This role identifies the <fen>Clothing</fen> that the <fen>Wearer</fen> wears.
The body part of the <fen>Wearer</fen> which is covered by the <fen>Clothing</fen>.
The time at or during which the <fen>Wearer</fen> has the <fen>Clothing</fen> on.
<fen>Connector</fen> identifies the instrument used to attach and is usually expressed in a <ment>with</ment>-PP.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that comes to be attached to the <fen>Goal</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are tied together, resulting in their mutual attachment.
<fen>Goal</fen> identifies the location to which the <fen>Item</fen>(s) is attached.
listRoleExamples: They had all just merged <fex>into one big file</fex>.
<fex>The single smaller soul</fex> merges with the Ur-soul.
The single smaller soul merges <fex>with the Ur-soul</fex>.
He tied <fex>an electrical cable</fex> around the trunk and his neck before hanging himself .
Jake tied the cravat <fex>into an acceptable knot</fex>.
Terri tied the rope around her waist <fex>before scrambling up the side of the mountain</fex>.
Rebels set three prisoners free <fex>from holding cells</fex>.
'Aren't you going to free us <fex>here</fex>?' she asked.
She was wearing a glove <fex>on one hand</fex>.
<fex>By five o'clock</fex>, he was wearing the old holey jeans and t-shirt again.
The tarp is  tied down <fex>with a rope</fex>.
<fex>A handle</fex>  was affixed to the door.
The boat remained anchored <fex>to the coastline</fex>.
